1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:04,762
Wait, what if the best musicians of the future can’t play a single note?

2
00:00:04,762 --> 00:00:09,350
For all of human history, music required physical dexterity.

3
00:00:09,350 --> 00:00:14,187
If you couldn’t move your fingers fast enough, the symphony stayed in your head.

4
00:00:14,187 --> 00:00:16,900
That barrier is officially gone.

5
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:23,662
AI is doing for music what photography did for painting: it’s decoupling the *idea* from the *execution*.

6
00:00:23,662 --> 00:00:27,125
The new instrument isn't a guitar, it's a model.

7
00:00:27,125 --> 00:00:30,775
You don't need music theory; you just need taste.

8
00:00:30,775 --> 00:00:36,175
When the technical barrier drops to zero, taste is the only differentiator left.

9
00:00:36,175 --> 00:00:41,275
We are about to unlock a flood of genius previously trapped by a lack of skill.

10
00:00:41,275 --> 00:00:45,562
We are moving from an era of performance to an era of curation.

11
00:00:45,562 --> 00:00:51,925
The non-musician is rising, and the music they make might be the most interesting thing we’ve heard in years.

12
00:00:51,925 --> 00:00:53,437
Get ready.

